name: "Stone Bunny" by Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
description: [Ink on notebook page with digital embellishments and color.] This ancient stone statue represents Xenu, the Bunny God, who was worshiped by the Cave People of North America from time immemorial. Xenu is said to have the power to change shape, cloud the minds of men, and communicate with the Sasquatch people. He is also very good at cards and other forms of gambling. ---Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
